text: For those who are making fun of this story please read. I am from a one of a big cities in Pakistan. Back in 2001, we moved to a new apartment in a newly built building in the suburb called Soldier Bzaar and I got admission in a near by school where I met a boy named Faisal and we became good friends. he belongs from a lower-middle class family and lived in a small house in a so called slum. I went to his house a couple of times for homework and studies in the day time and it looked absolutel  fine. one day he told me a revealed a secret that whenever someone get up anytime between 2am-5am they find someone around them. whispering something in agony. I ignored it and laughed at him because I didn't have any idea if those things exist or not because I was like 14. just before our annual exams I went to his house for last day preparation. there were two rooms upstairs. one was locked and another one was his in which we were studying. We were tired and decided to sleep. late at around 3am I got up thirsty and went down to the kitchen to get some water. by the time I opened the tap some invisible thing hit me hard on my neck. I could only smell its bad odour but there was no one around me. I was screaming for help but my mouth and lips were not moving. it was like I was screaming in my head but unable to deliver it from mouth. like something was controlling my body and brain functions. I don't know what happened next but I was found in my bed with a really bad bruise on my neck and the back of my head. I explained it to a religious person/priest and they don't want to investigate this thing in my friends house because it believed that that thing has been there since more than 100 years and borns every night after 2 hours of night prayers at around 10pm and dies or goes away just before the morning prayers 5am.

You can just smash them against the wall and be done with it. text: I had a porcelain doll I got for christmas when I was a little girl. After a few weeks I had given her to my mom and told her I did not want her anymore. Years and years later I had forgotten until I found her in my moms crawl space. I thought, "why not bring her back out and have her in my room?" BIG MISTAKE. I swear this doll had some horrible energy. I felt like I was constantly being watched and could FEEL her. I felt like she had the presence of an actual person. I became so afraid of her... I didn't want to throw her away or move her because I was afraid. I genuinely felt their was evil attached to this doll, and it had a very controlling hold on me. (Sounds weird, but you'd have to experience it)  I eventually told my boyfriend at the time and he could tell how afraid/upset I was. He decided he'd take the doll and get rid of it for me. Thank God for him. The moment she was gone I felt so much more at peace. =_=

text: I've been doing a horror movie script for a trailer and was wondering if anyone could give me some feedback.  FADE IN: SCENE 1: INT. CHRIS‚ÄôS ROOM ‚Äì DAY Chris is in his room accounting experiences of his. Chris ‚ÄúFebruary 4, 2016, my first log. A few months ago we moved to a house we now call our home. The house was amazing, better than I could have ever hoped for. Me and my Dad celebrated with a nice meal out to the Keg. He bought me a new game as well: Call of Duty Black ops 3. Lately I‚Äôve been getting into that game. Maybe a little too much.‚Äù SCENE 2: INT. HAUNTED HOUSE ‚Äì NIGHT Tap water is dripping from sink. Transitions to Chris staring at a monitor, playing the newest Call of Duty. While he is doing so, a large thump comes from downstairs. Chris takes off his headphones in concern. He goes back to playing. Panning shot of hallway that ends focused on door Chris‚Äôs room. Shot of Chris staring at monitor. While focusing on Chris, Suddenly, a huge bang immediately comes from downstairs. Chris takes off headphones, gets out of chair opens the door and walks up to the stairwell.  Chris: ‚ÄúDad?‚Äù He notices that his Dad‚Äôs door is closed. He walks cautiously down the stairs. The lights are on, chairs are tossed on the floor, cabinet doors are flung open, fridge and food supplies are all on the ground. He looks in shock. SCENE 3: EXT. OUT IN THE WOODS ‚Äì NIGHT Chris: ‚ÄúFebruary 27, 2016. Ever since that day, things have never been the same.‚Äù Transition to woods out in the middle of nowhere during the night. Chris is running in fear. Chris: ‚ÄúI keep having this re-occurring nightmare. I am in the forest running from this thing this entity. Describing it in words is not possible. The amount of evil intent and fear this thing brings to me is not something I like to talk about. I try to run but it always gets closer. At the end of this nightmare, I am engulfed in a struggle as whatever this entity is, tries to take my soul. After that, I am engulfed in darkness, than I wake up.  SCENE 3: TAKES PLACE IN HOME ‚Äì EVENING Chris is walking downstairs. Chris starts hearing children‚Äôs voices coming from downstairs. He opens the door. The voices immediately stop. He walks down the stairs. After he sees nothing downstairs he starts walking back upstairs. The door slams shut and Chris darts up the stairs pounding on the door. The voices come back slowly getting closer and closer to Chris. A shot of the basement door wile Chris is screaming for help. text: It's a decent thriller, if you're on the fence about giving "The Boy" a try. The film is steeped in that old school "creepy sprawling English mansion" vibe, and the plot is not bad or lame. It could have been one of those spooky Hammer Studio films of the 1960s. It pulls you in with its creepy mood/pacing and a sensation of dread. The ending was not simply tacked on; there are hints/clues along the way that you "get" on the second viewing.  Add a star if you liked Bella from "Supernatural". Ugh, yet another cool female character they killed off that show.  So it's much more than what some people would call "Annabelle and Chucky's new playmate", ha ha ha. If you're a fan of a slow and chilling fright flick, one that gets under your skin, this might be worthwhile.
